The paper deals with the problem of computing a sample mean of time series under dynamic time warping, which is a common problem in time series analysis. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also proposes a generic algorithm for solving the problem, which involves alternating between averaging and compression steps. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category, as the algorithm could be seen as a type of unsupervised learning. Additionally, the paper mentions that the algorithm can be applied to time series data in computer vision and artificial intelligence, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions that the algorithm involves compression of the approximate solution, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category, as compression is a common topic in information theory.
